#. <section class="sutta" id="sn31.13"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn31.13-22:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 31"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 31"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn31.13-22:0.2"
msgid "1. Gandhabbavagga"
msgstr "1. Fairies"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 13–​22. Mūlagandhadānūpakārasuttadasaka → dānupakārā 1 (pts1)
msgctxt "sn31.13-22:0.3"
msgid "13–​22. Mūlagandhadānūpakārasuttadasaka"
msgstr ""
"13–22. Ten Discourses On How Giving Helps to Become a Fragrant Root Fairy"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn31.13-22:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthinidānaṃ."
msgstr "At Sāvatthī."

msgctxt "sn31.13-22:1.2"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho so bhikkhu bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "Seated to one side, that mendicant said to the Buddha:"

msgctxt "sn31.13-22:1.3"
msgid ""
"“ko nu kho, bhante, hetu, ko paccayo, yena midhekacco kāyassa bhedā paraṃ "
"maraṇā mūlagandhe adhivatthānaṃ devānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjatī”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“Sir, what is the cause, what is the reason why someone, when their body "
"breaks up, after death, is reborn in the company of the gods of fairykind "
"who live in fragrant roots?”"

msgctxt "sn31.13-22:1.4"
msgid ""
"“Idha, bhikkhu, ekacco kāyena sucaritaṃ carati, vācāya sucaritaṃ carati, "
"manasā sucaritaṃ carati."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicant, it’s when someone does good things by way of body, speech, and "
"mind."

msgctxt "sn31.13-22:1.5"
msgid "Tassa sutaṃ hoti:"
msgstr "And they’ve heard:"

msgctxt "sn31.13-22:1.6"
msgid "‘mūlagandhe adhivatthā devā dīghāyukā vaṇṇavanto sukhabahulā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘The gods of fairykind who live in fragrant roots are long-lived, beautiful, "
"and very happy.’"

msgctxt "sn31.13-22:1.7"
msgid "Tassa evaṃ hoti:"
msgstr "They think:"

msgctxt "sn31.13-22:1.8"
msgid ""
"‘aho vatāhaṃ kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā mūlagandhe adhivatthānaṃ devānaṃ "
"sahabyataṃ upapajjeyyan’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘If only, when my body breaks up, after death, I would be reborn in the "
"company of the gods of fairykind who live in fragrant roots!’"

msgctxt "sn31.13-22:1.9"
msgid "So annaṃ deti … pe …"
msgstr "They give food …"

msgctxt "sn31.13-22:1.10"
msgid "pānaṃ deti …"
msgstr "drink …"

msgctxt "sn31.13-22:1.11"
msgid "vatthaṃ deti …"
msgstr "clothing …"

msgctxt "sn31.13-22:1.12"
msgid "yānaṃ deti …"
msgstr "a vehicle …"

msgctxt "sn31.13-22:1.13"
msgid "mālaṃ deti …"
msgstr "a garland …"

msgctxt "sn31.13-22:1.14"
msgid "gandhaṃ deti …"
msgstr "fragrance …"

msgctxt "sn31.13-22:1.15"
msgid "vilepanaṃ deti …"
msgstr "makeup …"

msgctxt "sn31.13-22:1.16"
msgid "seyyaṃ deti …"
msgstr "a bed …"

msgctxt "sn31.13-22:1.17"
msgid "āvasathaṃ deti …"
msgstr "a house …"

msgctxt "sn31.13-22:1.18"
msgid "padīpeyyaṃ deti."
msgstr "a lamp."

msgctxt "sn31.13-22:1.19"
msgid ""
"So kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā mūlagandhe adhivatthānaṃ devānaṃ sahabyataṃ "
"upapajjati."
msgstr ""
"When their body breaks up, after death, they’re reborn in the company of the "
"gods of fairykind who live in fragrant roots."

msgctxt "sn31.13-22:1.20"
msgid ""
"Ayaṃ kho, bhikkhu, hetu, ayaṃ paccayo, yena midhekacco kāyassa bhedā paraṃ "
"maraṇā mūlagandhe adhivatthānaṃ devānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjatī”ti."
msgstr ""
"This is the cause, this is the reason why someone, when their body breaks "
"up, after death, is reborn in the company of the gods of fairykind who live "
"on fragrant scents.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn31.13-22:1.21"
msgid "Bāvīsatimaṃ."
msgstr ""
